processes.name: Select Services
processes.description:
Customer Selects required services (Maintenance, Accessories, Central or Local Packages) in a structured way to the Customer. The customer can select from the catalog and the selected items are added to the appointment. 

The products offered to the customer also include upselling possibilities.

processes.name: Display Invoice
processes.description: The invoice is displayed to the customer

processes.name: Notification for Check-In
processes.description: The user gets notified about an upcoming appointment via a mobile app push notification or SMS depending on the personal preference of the user

processes.name: Confirm Personal Details
processes.description: The customer confirms/corrects his personal details, the details of the vehicle and the dealer

processes.name: Online Payment
processes.description: The customer pays the invoice online

processes.name: Personal Data Verification
processes.description: The personal data of the user is being shown. The user can confirm or correct the data.

processes.name: Additional Offers
processes.description: Show additional offers to the user beside the current - already selected - services

processes.name: Check-In Summary
processes.description: The summary of the appointment/order is being shown to the user for final review.

processes.name: Guided Order Creation
processes.description: Guided Order Creation creates an order from a customer statement using the technical documentation of a vehicle
processes.input: Customer Statement, Vehicle Information and Vehicle Condition

processes.name: Appointment Booking
processes.description: The appointment booking process is executed by a customer to book a service appointment at a dealership

processes.name: Load Booking Details
processes.description: This process step prepares the online booking. It loads the details of the dealer, vehicle and customer and usually displays an overview of those entities to the user.
processes.input: Dealer Id, Customer Id, Vehicle Id

processes.name: Pre Check-In
processes.description: Pre Check-In lets the user confirm the appointment details in advance and gives the dealer an upsell possibility.

processes.name: Order Extension
processes.description: Something was detected during the repair of the vehicle.

processes.name: Select Appointment Slots
processes.description: Based on the current appointment configuration, free appointment slots are being loaded and shown to the customer

processes.name: Service Appointment Data Verification
processes.description: The appointment details are shown to the user (Services, Drop-Off-Method, Replacement Mobility,...). The user can confirm or modify the details.

processes.name: Digital Signature / Confirmation
processes.description: The user confirms the appointment and changes he agrees to pay for the order and the order status is changed to check-in

processes.name: App or Portal
processes.description: User logs in to the Brand portal or the app.

processes.name: Select Payment Details
processes.description: The customer selects the details of the payment

processes.name: Information about corresponding offer
processes.description: Package and Price estimate

processes.name: Additional Comments
processes.description: Let the user specify any additional comments that should be stored at the appointment. The comment is visible to the service advisor.

processes.name: Select Appointment Configuration
processes.description: Customer selects drop-off method & replacement mobility.

processes.name: Appointment/Order Status Tracking
processes.description:
The Order Status tracking shows the current Appointment/Order Status to the user depending of the status tracking configuration. 

The following checkpoints should be available:
- Appointment Booking
- Order Preparation
- Pre Check-In
- Waiting for Vehicle Drop-Off
- Service in Progress
- Waiting for Vehicle Pick-Up

The following notifications should be sent:
- Appointment confirmed
- Pre-Check-In conducted
- Vehicle received
- Service in progress
- Ready for Pick-Up/Payment

processes.name: Payment confirmation
processes.description: The payment is confirmed

processes.name: Booking Confirmation
processes.description: A Booking confirmation is shown to the user. The user can review the booking and download a calendar entry

apiCalls.name: getDealerStatusTrackingConfiguration
apiCalls.description: Returns the configuration, which service events should be shown to the user

apiCalls.name: orderUpdatedNotification
apiCalls.description: The Order Management System detected an Order update and informs the subscribed consumers

apiCalls.name: bookAppointment
apiCalls.input: Selected Services, Appointment, CustomerId, Vin, Dealer

apiCalls.name: SBO - getServices
apiCalls.description: Loads a list of all services based on provided by the booking system to be shown to the user
